==English==

===Adjective===
'''awesome''', '''more awesome''', '''most awesome'''

# (''somewhat dated or formal'') Causing [[awe]] or terror.
#: ''The waterfall in the middle of the rainforest was an awesome sight''.
#: ''The tsunami was awesome in its destructive power.''
# (''colloquial'') Excellent, exciting.
#: ''That concert was awesome!''

===Noun===
# (''description beyond description'') Referring to one called Jessica
#: ''Awesome is coming to visit later this evening''.
